<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-126] Incorrect IOException in SequenceFile when BF returns false positive</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-126</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In SequenceFile.AbstractReader.seekTo(), an IOException is thrown when a key can&apos;t be found in an SSTable. This is incorrect. The BF associated with the SSTable could return a false positive. So a key may indeed not be present in the SSTable file. We need to handle this case accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12424341">CASSANDRA-126</key>
            <summary>Incorrect IOException in SequenceFile when BF returns false positive</summary>
